## Settings Panel Implementation - Detailed Analysis

I've thoroughly examined both readers. Here's a comprehensive breakdown of how the settings panel works in ScrollReader and PaginatedReader:

---

### 1. SETTINGS TOGGLE BUTTON AND CLICK HANDLER

#### ScrollReader (lines 416-438)
```jsx
<button
  class="pressy-settings-toggle"
  onClick={(e: MouseEvent) => {
    e.stopPropagation();
    setTocOpen(false);                  // Close TOC when opening settings
    setSettingsOpen(!settingsOpen);      // Toggle settings
  }}
  aria-label="Settings"
>
  <svg>/* gear icon */</svg>
</button>
```

#### PaginatedReader (lines 1347-1369)
```jsx
<button
  class="pressy-settings-toggle"
  onClick={(e: MouseEvent) => {
    e.stopPropagation();
    setTocOpen(false);                  // Close TOC when opening settings
    setSettingsOpen(!settingsOpen);      // Toggle settings
  }}
  aria-label="Settings"
>
  <svg>/* gear icon */</svg>
</button>
```

**Key Pattern:** Both readers have identical click handlers that:
- Call `e.stopPropagation()` to prevent bubbling to the footer or container
- Close TOC before opening settings (mutually exclusive panels)
- Toggle `settingsOpen` state

---

### 2. SETTINGS PANEL JSX

#### ScrollReader (lines 441-582)
```jsx
<div
  class={`pressy-settings-panel ${
    settingsOpen ? "pressy-settings-panel--open" : ""
  }`}
>
  <div class="pressy-settings-section">
    <div class="pressy-settings-label">Theme</div>
    <div class="pressy-theme-options">
      {/* 4 theme buttons: light, dark, system, sepia */}
      {[...].map((t) => (
        <button
          key={t.id}
          class={`pressy-theme-btn ${
            activeTheme === t.id ? "pressy-theme-btn--active" : ""
          }`}
          onClick={(e: MouseEvent) => {
            e.stopPropagation();
            handleThemeChange(t.id);
          }}
        >
          {t.icon}
          <span>{t.label}</span>
        </button>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pressy-settings-section">
    <div class="pressy-settings-label">Font Size</div>
    <div class="pressy-font-size-controls">
      <button
        class="pressy-font-size-btn"
        onClick={(e: MouseEvent) => {
          e.stopPropagation();
          handleFontSizeChange(-0.1);
        }}
        disabled={fontScale <= 0.8}
        aria-label="Decrease font size"
      >
        A-
      </button>
      <span class="pressy-font-size-value">
        {Math.round(fontScale * 100)}%
      </span>
      <button
        class="pressy-font-size-btn"
        onClick={(e: MouseEvent) => {
          e.stopPropagation();
          handleFontSizeChange(0.1);
        }}
        disabled={fontScale >= 1.5}
        aria-label="Increase font size"
      >
        A+
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

#### PaginatedReader (lines 1372-1513)
**Identical structure** to ScrollReader - same sections, buttons, and layout.

**Key Points:**
- The panel contains `.pressy-settings-section` divs
- Each section has a `.pressy-settings-label` and controls
- Classes conditionally add `--open` modifier when `settingsOpen === true`
- All buttons call `e.stopPropagation()` to prevent closing the panel
- Theme buttons show icons + labels, disable based on `activeTheme` state
- Font size buttons have `disabled` attribute when at min/max bounds

---

### 3. STATE MANAGEMENT FOR SETTINGS/TOC INTERACTION

#### ScrollReader (lines 131-132)
```typescript
const [settingsOpen, setSettingsOpen] = useState(false);
const [tocOpen, setTocOpen] = useState(false);
```

#### PaginatedReader (lines 137-138)
```typescript
const [settingsOpen, setSettingsOpen] = useState(false);
const [tocOpen, setTocOpen] = useState(false);
```

**Mutual Exclusivity Pattern:**
Both panels are **mutually exclusive** - opening one closes the other:

**ScrollReader TOC toggle (lines 376-382):**
```jsx
<button
  class="pressy-toc-toggle"
  onClick={(e: MouseEvent) => {
    e.stopPropagation();
    setSettingsOpen(false);    // Close settings when opening TOC
    setTocOpen(!tocOpen);
  }}
/>
```

**PaginatedReader TOC toggle (lines 1307-1313):**
```jsx
